  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>thick chips</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>thick chips</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled wate</strong>r and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5 min, then drain and rinse with cold water to cool them slightly (save the pot!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1700570878091-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1700570878091-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1700570878091-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1700570878091-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1700570878091-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Add the <strong>par-boiled chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>twice cooked chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700570882658-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700570882658-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700570882658-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700570882658-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700570882658-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reserve one sprig of<strong> rosemary</strong>, then strip the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Crush your<strong> garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin[s]</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700570888036-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700570888036-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700570888036-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700570888036-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700570888036-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped rosemary</strong>,<strong> crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>crispy onions </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Blitz until you are left with a smooth paste – this is your <strong>onion & rosemary butter</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700570893162-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700570893162-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700570893162-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700570893162-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700570893162-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until they’re starting to soften</p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt, rinse under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool and squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
